records.name: The Barefoot Eco Hotel

descriptions.direction: Located in Hanimaadhoo, The Barefoot Eco Hotel is near the airport and on a private beach. Local points of interest include Maldives Climate Observatory, Baarah Dock, and Utheemu Palace. Take an opportunity to explore the area for outdoor excitement like hiking/biking trails and other activities like safari tours.
descriptions.general: This 4 star eco-friendly hotel is located within an almost untouched forest on Hanimadhoo island in the preserved deep North of Maldives. Well connected to Male international airport by numerous daily flights, this complex invests major efforts in reducing its carbon footprint offering all the comforts for a truly relaxing stay. Due to its luxuriant vegetation and privacy everybody can fall in an untouched nature, living the genuine and natural Maldives with all modern accommodation facilities. A long private sandy beach and a turquoise lagoon frame the hotel, making it ideal to forget daily stress. As for the accommodation units, they all have been designed to suit all guests' needs, ranging from the seaside rooms to the beachfront villa. The onsite dining options include a sea view restaurant and panoramic bar, whilst the diving centre offers guests the chance to explore the Maldivian underwater world.
